Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.77,0:01:00.82,LC注释FHD,,0,0,0,,注:\hthe Big C是2010年8月16日首播的美剧，Leftover Cuties第一部专辑Game Called Life EP发布于2009年\N\h\h\h\h\h(EP指extended-playing record，歌曲数量介于单曲single和专辑album之间，一般是正式专辑发布前的试水作)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.59,0:01:38.71,LC注释FHD,,0,0,0,,注:\hRyan Hewitt is an American music producer, engineer and mixer known for his work with The Lumineers, \N\h\h\h\h\hRed Hot Chili Peppers, The Avett Brothers, The Dixie Chicks, Third Eye Blind, Jamie Cullum, John Frusciante \N\h\h\h\h\hand the Turnpike Troubadours.\N\h\h\h\h\h以上截自维基百科，大概就是一个很有名的音乐制作人
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.62,0:03:31.97,LC注释FHD,,0,0,0,,注:\h这个视频在2011年5月25日发布的，指的专辑应该是这个时间附近发布的Places To Go，而EP指的是Game Called Life EP
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.37,0:00:31.08,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,I came over to Shirli's house in the middle of the night with a ukulele.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.14,0:00:33.34,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,He was playing this beautiful chord change
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.40,0:00:34.51,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,and I was like "what's that?".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.54,0:00:36.11,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,I don't remember exactly what she said
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.32,0:00:39.26,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,but it was like "Is that a real instrument?".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.26,0:00:41.97,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,And I was like "Yeah, it's a real trend now. A lot of people run it off as a toy".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.02,0:00:45.14,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,I had witnessed similarly except night at the bar I was working at.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.88,0:00:47.31,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,So I pulled the lyrics out
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.31,0:00:49.77,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,and I started singing over whatever he was playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.80,0:00:53.77,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,And we wrote Game Called Life in about five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.77,0:00:57.57,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,Having Game Called Life as a theme song for the Big C.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.17,0:00:59.57,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,It's been incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.57,0:01:00.82,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,Overwhelming, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.85,0:01:04.94,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,I wrote that song kind of wondering what the hell am I doing with my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.02,0:01:11.25,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,To realize that somebody that has been diagnosed with cancer can relate to it on that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.34,0:01:16.74,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,I felt like the song did something greater than I meant for it to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.02,0:01:24.11,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,Then started with Austin and I basically writing songs and recording little demos at my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.57,0:01:26.68,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,Just with the ukulele, my vocals.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:31.02,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,With that couples of noise makers, shakers or kazoo or whatever was lying around the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.14,0:01:35.34,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,We thought there was a certain charm to the way was so raw and so broken down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.59,0:01:38.71,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,You know when time had passed we sought out Ryan Hewitt.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.74,0:01:40.51,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,And he was like "All these are great songs".
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.54,0:01:43.77,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,"But if you guys want to sell records you're gonna need to get some drums."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.05,0:01:47.51,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,A light came on Shirli(?) and I said like "I know the drummer that's perfect for this".
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.14,0:01:49.28,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,It was Stuart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.40,0:01:51.77,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,One of the most musical drummers I've ever met.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.85,0:01:53.74,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,We went over to his house and...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.80,0:01:55.31,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,Look Ok. Play something for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.88,0:01:57.02,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,She played the song and music.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.34,0:01:58.85,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,It's some kind of sad that he didn't say much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.45,0:02:00.65,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,And he said, "Hold on."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.71,0:02:02.31,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,He ran his house, started grabbing some stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.37,0:02:05.62,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,Back in stuck around like throwing pots and pans down or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.68,0:02:10.82,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,When I heard ukulele being played I thought what can I played not to overpower that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.88,0:02:13.80,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,Drums could crush a ukulele pretty quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.87,0:02:17.74,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,but I found some old drums that have calfskin heads on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.77,0:02:20.34,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,They're not plastic they have a warmer sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.73,0:02:23.04,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,For surely to flow to vocal over top of.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.20,0:02:23.77,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,It worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.85,0:02:27.42,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,At that point Stuart have heard our songs maybe a couple of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.48,0:02:32.00,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,So he basically was coming up with ideas and parts on the spot
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.02,0:02:33.51,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,when we were at the studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.68,0:02:35.54,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,From there branched out to Ryan Feves.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.68,0:02:37.25,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,One day Austin call me,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.88,0:02:43.42,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,"hey, do you want to play bass in my ukulele band?"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.00,0:02:47.28,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,And the way it sounded had the picture in my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.51,0:02:49.40,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,A bunch of people with the abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.60,0:02:50.77,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,We had real event a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.97,0:02:52.94,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,He's almost too good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.25,0:02:57.22,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,Of a musician, has too good of chops to play in the Leftover Cuties.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:02:59.94,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,The most recent addition is Mike Bolgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.97,0:03:04.91,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,He's one of those guys that you can call up for anything any situation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.97,0:03:07.88,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,and he'll come and play exactly what you want to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.11,0:03:10.62,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,He was basically the missing piece, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.77,0:03:17.08,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,Once he got into the band, I think we all really felt like we finally have a full sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.62,0:03:29.74,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,The album, compared to the EP,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.80,0:03:31.97,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,it's just, it's grown.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.20,0:03:35.17,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,Leftover Cuties was a new place for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.28,0:03:40.62,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,It's a place where we could be free and express ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.65,0:03:44.88,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,and be playful and be light-hearted
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.94,0:03:47.82,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,and also deep and emotional.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.31,0:03:52.02,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,There's so many different elements to it and in so many places that it takes you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.11,0:03:53.34,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,And it's just the beginning, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.37,0:03:54.17,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,It's the first album.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.28,0:03:56.34,LC英文FHD,,0,0,0,,So, it's gonna be quite a ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.37,0:00:31.08,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,我半夜带着尤克里里去Shirli家
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.14,0:00:33.34,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,他弹奏着美妙的和弦
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.40,0:00:34.51,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,而我很吃惊地问道 这是什么
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.54,0:00:36.11,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,我不记得她具体说了什么
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.32,0:00:39.26,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,大概是像 这是真正的乐器吗 一类的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.26,0:00:41.97,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,然后我就这样回答 没错 尤克里里最近很风靡 许多人把它当玩具玩
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.02,0:00:45.14,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,这和我在酒吧的工作完全不同
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.88,0:00:47.31,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,所以我把歌词写了出来
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.31,0:00:49.77,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,然后根据Austin弹奏的音乐歌唱
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.80,0:00:53.77,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,我们差不多五分钟内就写好了Game Called Life这首歌
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.77,0:00:57.57,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,Game Called Life被选作电视剧the Big C的主题曲
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.17,0:00:59.57,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,确实难以想象
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.57,0:01:00.82,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,这真是令人不知所措
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.85,0:01:04.94,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,我创作这首歌曲的动机是感叹我这糟蹋的人生
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.02,0:01:11.25,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,这首歌被选中后我才意识到有些患有癌症的人也会为此共鸣
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.34,0:01:16.74,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,我认为这首歌比我预想的起到的意义更大
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.02,0:01:24.11,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,然后我和Austin继续在我家里为试制歌曲谱曲写词
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.57,0:01:26.68,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,只是尤克里里伴奏 我来演唱
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:31.02,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,当然还用到了家里的一些乐器 譬如沙铃 卡祖笛之类
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.14,0:01:35.34,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,我们相信原生和悲伤的风格肯定有不少魅力
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.59,0:01:38.71,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,过段时间后 我们找到了Ryan Hewitt
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.74,0:01:40.51,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,他说 这些都是很好的歌曲
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.54,0:01:43.77,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,但是你们想发行唱片的话还需要一点鼓声
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.05,0:01:47.51,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,我突然想起确实有一个鼓手适合这个位置
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.14,0:01:49.28,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,他就是Stuart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.40,0:01:51.77,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,我见过的最优音乐天赋的鼓手之一
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.85,0:01:53.74,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,我们去了他家
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.80,0:01:55.31,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,他说 看着不错 你们给我来一段
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.88,0:01:57.02,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,Shirli弹唱了一会
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.34,0:01:58.85,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,Stuart话说得很少 似乎不是很高兴
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.45,0:02:00.65,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,之后他说 等等
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.71,0:02:02.31,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,他跑回家里 找着些东西
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.37,0:02:05.62,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,似乎是卡住了 翻找了好多东西
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.68,0:02:10.82,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,听了尤克里里以后 我感觉我使用的乐器不应该压制住它的声音
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.88,0:02:13.80,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,而鼓声很容易盖过尤克里里的声音
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.87,0:02:17.74,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,不过我找到了一些用牛皮做的鼓
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.77,0:02:20.34,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,因为不是用塑料做的 所以声音温润一些
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.73,0:02:23.04,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,当然也不会盖过人声
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.20,0:02:23.77,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,这主意起作用了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.85,0:02:27.42,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,Stuart已经听我们的歌好几次了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.48,0:02:32.00,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,所以他基本上很快知道怎么做了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.02,0:02:33.51,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,当我们在工作室的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.68,0:02:35.54,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,之后我们找到了Ryan Feves
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.68,0:02:37.25,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,有天Austin打电话给我说
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.88,0:02:43.42,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,嘿 你想在我们乐队弹奏低音提琴吗
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.00,0:02:47.28,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,他说这话的时候 我就在想
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.51,0:02:49.40,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,这肯定是一群有才能的人
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.60,0:02:50.77,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,我们正式演出过几次
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.97,0:02:52.94,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,他实在太棒了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.25,0:02:57.22,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,作为一个音乐家 在Leftover Cuties里他擅长的乐器太多了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.28,0:02:59.94,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,最近加入的成员是Mike Bolgar
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.97,0:03:04.91,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,他是那种任何情况下都随叫随到的人
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.97,0:03:07.88,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,并且能弹奏出任何你想听到的音乐
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.11,0:03:10.62,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,他差不多就是我们乐队欠缺的那部分
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.77,0:03:17.08,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,当他加入乐队的时候 我觉得我们乐队终于完整了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.62,0:03:29.74,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,现在这个专辑 相比于EP
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.80,0:03:31.97,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,已经发展了很多
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.20,0:03:35.17,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,Leftover Cuties是我们所有人的新家
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.28,0:03:40.62,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,我们在这可以自由地表现自己
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.65,0:03:44.88,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,可以无忧无虑地开玩笑
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.94,0:03:47.82,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,也可以充满感情地深入表达
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.31,0:03:52.02,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,这个专辑每处都有不同的元素能打动你
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.11,0:03:53.34,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,而这仅仅是一个开始
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.37,0:03:54.17,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,这是我们的第一个专辑
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.28,0:03:56.34,LC中文FHD,,0,0,0,,所以这将是一段不错的旅途
